news.title: Macrotech Developers' profit jumps 2.7 times to Rs 475 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income grew to Rs 2,918.3 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year from Rs 1,671.8 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income up 9% to Rs 496 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Net Operating Income (NOI) increased 9 per cent to Rs 496 crore, from Rs 455 crore a year-ago, while distribution grew 5 per cent in the reported quarter to Rs 299 crore, from Rs 285 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Sand will be made available for free for poor in state: Jharkhand CM
news.para: "Several issues related to sand such as its unavailability for the poor and its high prices and impact on Abua Awas Yojana have come to our notice. I would like to inform the House that our government will make sand free for non-taxpayers in the state," he said.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net operating income up 7% to Rs 413 crore in Q1FY25
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, the company said it achieved retail Net Operating Income (NOI) of Rs 371.9 crore in April-June period of this fiscal, up 8 per cent from the year-ago period.

news.title: MMRDA tells HDIL to hand over 1,400 flats in Kurla buildings, Rs 35 crore in rent arrears
news.para: The notices were issued to the resolution professional of HDIL, a developer from the city facing insolvency proceedings, to hand over the 1,336 residential units and 50 commercial units in two buildings of Premier Compound in Kurla.

news.title: Carlyle to sell upto 6.4% stake in PNB Housing Finance for Rs 1,256 crore on July 30
news.para: According to a term sheet issued by IIFL Securities, Quality Investment Holdings, an entity of Carlyle, will sell 1.66 crore shares at a floor price of Rs 775 apiece, aiming to raise Rs 1,256 crore.

news.title: Roads not ready, Allahabad HC allows 'zero period' waiver for Sunshine Trade Tower
news.para: The court, however, clarified that the decision was specific to the project because of the “peculiar circumstances” around it and should not be considered a general precedent.

news.title: No need for anybody in India Cements to feel insecure: MD to staff
news.para: "No need for anybody in India Cements to feel insecure or threatened. The future is as solid as when I was head of the plant," said India Cements Vice Chairman and MD N Srinivasan.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to develop 2,576 sq meters land in Bandra West, Mumbai
news.para: Oberoi Realty expects to generate a free sale component of around 40,000 sq ft from the said land.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac's profit slumps 69% in Q1 FY25
news.para: The century-old paint-maker’s revenue for the quarter fell 1% on year to Rs 2,050.4 crore, while earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortization was flat at Rs 323.4 crores.

news.title: SC upholds order for refund of amount to buyers by Parsvnath Developers for delayed possession of flat
news.para: ​A bench of Justices B R Gavai and Sandeep Mehta enhanced the rate of interest from 9 per cent awarded by the NCDRC to 12 per cent, saying the home buyers were made to suffer for long for no fault of theirs.

news.title: ACC's net profit down 22.5% to Rs 361 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: ACC's revenue from operations was marginally lower at Rs 5,154.89 crore during the quarter under review. It was Rs 5,201.11 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Country Garden liquidation hearing adjourned to January next year, court says
news.para: Ever Credit Limited, a unit of Hong Kong-listed Kingboard Holdings, filed the liquidation petition against Country Garden in February for non-payment of a $205 million loan.

news.title: India Cements to remain listed entity, says UltraTech
news.para: Axis Capital, managing the open offer for UltraTech, in a copy of a public announcement, submitted to exchanges on Monday said, the leading cement player intends to acquire 8.05 crore shares of ICL, which is 26 per cent of the shareholding of the Chennai-based cement manufacturer.

news.title: Goa: SEZ land scam probe still incomplete after 10 years
news.para: In 2012, ACB registered a first information report (FIR) based on a complaint filed by Mandar Shirodkar, deputy general manager (law), Goa Industrial Development Corporation (GIDC), on “arbitrary and illegal allotment of land” to seven parties for SEZ.

news.title: Chennai development body to introduce deemed NOCs for highrise buildings
news.para: CMDA, which introduced online plan permission in May 2022, on average approves 70 plans every month and more than 70 highrise buildings every year. The numbers were 35 and 60 prior to 2022, say CMDA officials.

news.title: Shah Rukh's son buys two floors in Delhi building for Rs 37 crore
news.para: The family already owns the basement and ground floor of the building, where Khan and his wife Gauri used to live in the early days.

news.title: EQT emerges as top contender to acquire Aavas Financiers
news.para: EQT is competing with two other private equity peers, CVC Capital Partners and Bain Capital, ahead of binding offers that are expected early August as PE firms look to consolidate their position in the fast-growing sector.
